The following Python code is supposed to find all prime numbers up to n using the Sieve of Eratosthenes, but it contains three bugs. Identify and fix each bug, explain what each bug caused, and then optimize the corrected version to reduce memory usage by approximately 50%. Code: `def sieve(n):
    primes = [True] * n
    primes[0] = primes[1] = False
    for i in range(2, n):
        if primes[i]:
            for j in range(i, n, i):
                primes[j] = False
    return [i for i in range(n) if primes[i]]`
